git log --graph --format=format:'%C(bold blue)%h%C(reset) - %C(bold cyan)%aD%C(reset) %C(bold green)(%ar)%C(reset)%C(bold yellow)%d%C(reset)%n''%C(white)%s%C(reset) %C(bold white)â€” %an%C(reset)' --abbrev-commit --all

Alias it to something like:
git config alias.graph = log --graph ..etc..

For a quick way to get an overview of your current branches etc, use a bash alias
alias gl='git graph -10'

